{
  "texts": [
    "Following the same derivations as in Example 2.2, with m = θ *,",
    "Here again, we would seek for the exact optimizer in s, but for example s = √ d/n we obtain:",
    "Example 4.7 (Lipschitz loss and Uniform priors).",
    "We propose a variant of the previous example, with a different prior.",
    "We still assume Bernstein assumption with constant K, θ → ℓ(f θ (x), y) is L-Lipschitz for any (x, y), and this time Θ = {θ ∈ R d: ∥θ∥ ≤ B} and π is uniform on Θ."
  ]
}